  "prompt": "What should I do when people make fun of my shoes at school?",
  "response": "Here are some good ways to handle that situation:\n\n1. Stay confident and calm\n\u2022 Don't let their comments upset you\n\u2022 Don't react defensively or get angry\n\n2. Possible responses:\n\u2022 Ignore them if the comments are minor\n\u2022 Confidently say something like \"I like my shoes\" \n\u2022 Use humor to deflect the teasing\n\u2022 Ask them why it matters what shoes you wear\n\n3. If bullying continues:\n\u2022 Talk to a teacher or school counselor\n\u2022 Tell your parents\n\u2022 Ask friends for support\n\n4. Remember:\n\u2022 Your worth isn't determined by your shoes\n\u2022 People who make fun of others often have their own insecurities",
